{
  "texts": [
    "Large language models have great potential in smell detection and refactoring suggestions.",
    "Up to date, various deep learning techniques have been proposed to detect code smells, and/or to suggest solutions to identified code smells.",
    "However, to the best of my knowledge, large language models have not yet been applied to such tasks.",
    "Since large language models are good at understanding and generating source code, it is likely that they can be employed to format source code and to identify abnormal parts of source code (i.e., code smells).",
    "They may also be employed to discover (and measure) the relationship (like coupling, similarity, cohesion, and dependency) among software entities."
  ]
}